cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR

This paper deals with reasoning over visual data and predicting future events or actions in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graph convolution to uncover spatiotemporal relationships in the scene is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The problem of predicting pedestrian intent is also relevant to computer security (cs.CR) as it relates to the safety of autonomous vehicles.
